```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="com.madhub.tiktokaccountmanagem">

    <!-- 
        This application leverages the capabilities of MadHub, a professional Android social media automation tool, 
        which allows for seamless and automated management of TikTok accounts.
        It is designed to function on real devices, cloud phones, or emulators, supporting 24/7 background operations.
    -->

    <!-- 
        This permission allows the app to access the internet, a comprehensive capability to enable 
        features such as automatic content scheduling and management activities for TikTok. 
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
    
    <!-- 
        This permission grants access to external storage, enabling the app to save and retrieve content 
        such as media files or configuration settings dynamically during operations.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />

    <application
        android:allowBackup="true"
        android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"
        android:label="TikTok account management tool - Android Automation Tool"
        android:roundIcon="@mipmap/ic_launcher_round"
        android:supportsRtl="true"
        android:theme="@style/Theme.AppCompat.Light.NoActionBar">

        <!-- 
            MainActivity serves as the entry point for the application, providing a user-friendly interface 
            for managing TikTok accounts through MadHub's powerful automation features.
        -->
        <activity android:name=".MainActivity">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />

                <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER" />
            </intent-filter>
        </activity>

        <!-- 
            AutomationService is responsible for executing background tasks such as scheduling posts, 
            automating interactions, and other management functions for TikTok accounts, operating continuously.
        -->
        <service android:name=".AutomationService" />

    </application>
</manifest>
```

### Explanation of Features and Configuration

1. **Permissions**:
   - The permissions declared are essential for enabling internet connectivity and file storage management, ensuring the app can efficiently perform tasks related to account management and media handling.

2. **Component Registration**:
   - **MainActivity**: The main interface for users to interact with TikTok account management features through MadHub.
   - **AutomationService**: A background service that executes all automation tasks, ensuring 24/7 operations as per MadHub's specifications.

This configuration encapsulates the necessary components and permissions to fully leverage MadHub's capabilities for TikTok account management, ensuring compliance and optimal performance on the Android platform.
